		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">This project will investigate a number of distinct but linked questions in mathematical finance.  The first is to set up a very general equilibrium model for international trade, production and consumption, and to analyse it using techniques of stochastic optimal control, especially exploiting convex duality.  This hopefully will give insight into how the term structure of interest rates and exchange rates behave.  The next goal is to build some software to model the term structure of interest rates, and price derivatives from that.  At a more fundamental level, an alternative approach to the formation of prices in a pure-exchange economy will be investigated, and if time permits this will be expanded to take into account learning and spatial effects.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
